            <lb/>
If foul eyed pity dwellt within thy breast.&#xD;<lb/>
If soft humanity informd thy mind&#xD;<lb/>
Then wouldst thou not deprive my soul of rest&#xD;<lb/>
My soul to woe and misery resignd&#xD;<lb/>
            <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">Ah</del> Thy cruel heart <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">is</del>
            <add xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0">must be as</add> hard as stone&#xD;<lb/>
To leave me thus unpitied and alone.&#xD;<lb/>
To leave me thus my &#xD;<lb/>
absence to bemoan&#xD;<lb/>
Ah when I think upon the dangrous seas&#xD;<lb/>
My heart is fill’d with agony and fear&#xD;<lb/>
Lest some <unclear xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0">xxxx</unclear> wind should sink thee in the deep&#xD;<lb/>
Lest some sharp toothed shark thy form should tear&#xD;<lb/>
Before my eyes all wet with briny tears&#xD;<lb/>
Pass the wan form of sorrows and of fears.&#xD;<lb/>
One single hope <unclear xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0">enlivens</unclear> my anxious soul&#xD;<lb/>
The hope that thou wilt <add xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0">shortly</add> come again&#xD;<lb/>
But all that hope that only hope is gone&#xD;<lb/>
            <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">But if that hope that only hope should fall.</del>
            <lb/>
I am the victim of despair and pain.&#xD;<lb/>
            <lb/>
