            <lb/>
32&#xD;<lb/>
That Hypothesis is much likelier to be false than true which is taken up&#xD;<lb/>
at a venture. Eternal &amp; immutable truth is it then that these Hypothetical&#xD;<lb/>
Reasoners seek after <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">do they think</del> to do they imagigine that thine&#xD;<lb/>
abode is in the gaudy &amp; embellished region of imagination&#xD;<lb/>
            <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">no they cannot imagine it; they cannot believe it</del> Then their&#xD;<lb/>
            <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">intention must be to deceive Mankind</del>
            <lb/>
            <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">In all our speculations</del> Truth shou’d be the sole object of&#xD;<lb/>
our Researches. She will ultimately tend to the benifit of mankind&#xD;<lb/>
She will remain eternal &amp; immutable&#xD;<lb/>
            <milestone xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                       unit="section"
                       rend="line"/>
            <lb/>
Tho the specious fables of Hypocritical Falshood may endure for&#xD;<lb/>
a while tho’ they may for a while mislead the Human <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">Mind</del>
            <lb/>
naturally attached to gaudy &amp; imbellished Hypothesis. Yet the&#xD;<lb/>
Light of truth steady &amp; uniform in its progress &amp; immutable&#xD;<lb/>
in its appearance will at length shine forth in spite of all the&#xD;<lb/>
difficulties which appear to embarras it. Truth is eternal&#xD;<lb/>
Falshood is transitority. Truth woud exist tho’ Man existed&#xD;<lb/>
not Falshood exists in Man. Falshood ultimately tends to the&#xD;<lb/>
Misery <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">of Man</del> Truth to the Happiness of Man. –&#xD;<lb/>
Shall we not then search after such an object shall we&#xD;<lb/>
not endeavour to investigate Her &amp; to overthrow the obstacles&#xD;<lb/>
which hide her from our view —&#xD;<lb/>
            <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">Those obstacles are Credulity &amp; prejudi</del>ce. The Chains by&#xD;<lb/>
which the human Mind is enfettered are Credulity &amp; prejudice.&#xD;<lb/>
            <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">The progress of Truth &amp; Science have been very much impeded</del>
            <lb/>
The Consideration of certain Opinions as Dangerous has&#xD;<lb/>
been one of the Chief Obstacles to the Progress of&#xD;<lb/>
Truth &amp; Science&#xD;<lb/>
Falshood like the <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag13"
                ref="#misc_278"
                type="miscellaneous">
               <term xml:id="tag13">
          Ignis Fatuus
        </term>
            </rs> shining with&#xD;<lb/>
a weak tho’ Glaring light <add xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0">changing &amp; wavering</add> finally deceives&#xD;<lb/>
&amp; bewilders the unhappy Traveller allured&#xD;<lb/>
by its brightness. <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">Truth</del> The light of truth&#xD;<lb/>
steady &amp; uniform in its appearances bright&#xD;<lb/>
as the Meridian Sun never fails to Conduct&#xD;<lb/>
its follower to the port of Happiness&#xD;<lb/>
            <lb/>
