may fix all its attention on an absent Object &amp; may not.&#xD;<lb/>
the intense desire the idea still directed still applied&#xD;<lb/>
by wish to the absent object. reach <add xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0">it</add> not withstanding&#xD;<lb/>
all obstacles, may not the Mind agitated by agony at&#xD;<lb/>
the hour of Death assume a more than common&#xD;<lb/>
power &amp; by an unknown Energy act upon a distant&#xD;<lb/>
Object who is influenced by the same passion &amp; who&#xD;<lb/>
eagerly pines for an interview. The state of Sympathy&#xD;<lb/>
in the minds of both renders the event more likely –&#xD;<lb/>
May not the imagination of the dying Person operating&#xD;<lb/>
in this manner on the imagination of her lover or &#xD;<lb/>
Friend produce an Idea resembling the real&#xD;<lb/>
appearance this Theory tho’ it may appear at&#xD;<lb/>
first view visionary demands real attention&#xD;<lb/>
