                 rend="strikethrough">Author of Existence</del> We must suppose&#xD;<lb/>
that He had some End in view &amp; this End proceeding&#xD;<lb/>
from the Will of such a being must have been the&#xD;<lb/>
the best possible – but the best possible End of Being&#xD;<lb/>
is Happiness –&#xD;<lb/>
But Man is subject to both pain &amp; Pleasure, He cou’d&#xD;<lb/>
not therefore Exist without Both –&#xD;<lb/>
For if He had neither of these Sensations He might as&#xD;<lb/>
well have never been organized. There being no motives&#xD;<lb/>
to Act – He coud never act. for we cannot conceive Action&#xD;<lb/>
without Motive –&#xD;<lb/>
It is the Nature of Organized beings to perceive&#xD;<lb/>
