            <lb/>
4. Nations are similar in their Manners &amp; Character in&#xD;<lb/>
Proportion as their Countries are Contiguous &amp; their&#xD;<lb/>
Climates similar. In the greater part of Southern Asia.&#xD;<lb/>
the Climate is warm &amp; the air salubrious though sultry.&#xD;<lb/>
(ie all the Southern Asiatics)&#xD;<lb/>
all the Inhabitants of Southern Asia. are effeminate in&#xD;<lb/>
the Extreme, fond of Indolence &amp; never act but with Reluctance&#xD;<lb/>
And <add xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0">this</add> similarity of Manners &amp; Character is not to be attributed&#xD;<lb/>
to Moral Causes. For the Government Religion &amp; mode of&#xD;<lb/>
Education are different in <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag177"
                ref="#place_873"
                type="place">
               <name xml:id="tag177" type="place">
          Persia
        </name>
            </rs> &amp; <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag178"
                ref="#misc_295"
                type="miscellaneous">
               <term xml:id="tag178">
          Indostan
        </term>
            </rs>. yet the&#xD;<lb/>
Natives of Both. are <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">stamped</del> characterized by the Climat.&#xD;<lb/>
with Indolence &amp; Luxury.&#xD;<lb/>
The Northern Asiatics on the Contrary who inhabit the&#xD;<lb/>
extensive Regions of <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag179"
                ref="#misc_292"
                type="miscellaneous">
               <term xml:id="tag179">
          Tartary
        </term>
            </rs>. tho’ acted on by the same&#xD;<lb/>
moral Causes as the southern Asiatics, having similar&#xD;<lb/>
Governments &amp; institutions. resemble the <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag180"
                ref="#misc_296"
                type="miscellaneous">
               <term xml:id="tag180">
          Muscovites
        </term>
            </rs> &amp;&#xD;<lb/>
the Inhabitants of the Northern Countries of Europe.&#xD;<lb/>
in their Manners &amp; Character. Totally unlike the Southern&#xD;<lb/>
Nations They are strong, robust &amp; active – &amp;c –&#xD;<lb/>
Indeed the Manners &amp; Characters of the European Nations&#xD;<lb/>
are similar. in proportion as the Climates are like.&#xD;<lb/>
after accounting for the differences occasioned by Moral&#xD;<lb/>
Causes. We find a greater Resemblance between <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
