4 A Nation emigrating from a cold Country where&#xD;<lb/>
where their only means of Subsistence were procured&#xD;<lb/>
by labour or the Chace into a mild &amp; more&#xD;<lb/>
temperate Climat where the Earth inspontaneously&#xD;<lb/>
produced every thing necessary for their Subsistence&#xD;<lb/>
woud have a very great difference in their present&#xD;<lb/>
&amp; former Manners &amp; Character. Formerly obliged to&#xD;<lb/>
