The Error of this Opinion is easily discerned if we only&#xD;<lb/>
take a view of the various nations of the Earth –&#xD;<lb/>
We shall find that similarity of <del xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                 rend="strikethrough">Codes</del> of Codes of&#xD;<lb/>
Education Religion &amp; politics do not always constitute&#xD;<lb/>
similarity of Character indeed in distant provinces&#xD;<lb/>
of the Same Nation where the Same laws &amp; Customs&#xD;<lb/>
prevail the Character is often very different –&#xD;<lb/>
This difference then must be owing to Climat –&#xD;<lb/>
The Manners &amp; Character of Man is formed by his Sensations&#xD;<lb/>
Affections &amp; Wants: But all of these are influenced&#xD;<lb/>
by the Climat &amp; of course his Manners &amp; Character&#xD;<lb/>
are influenced by the Climat –&#xD;<lb/>
